syncmoo1 -- Master of Orion 1 for Synchronet / SyncTERM (and any DOOR32.SYS BBS)
=================================================================================

syncmoo1 is GPL-2.0, built on and incorporating the following GPL-2.0 works.
See each upstream project for full copyright and license text.

Engine (vendored in this directory, 1oom/)
-------------------------------------------
- 1oom -- the fork1oom/1oom line (https://sourcecraft.dev/fork1oom/1oom;
  GitHub is a mirror). (GPL-2.0)
  A portable, faithful reimplementation of Master of Orion 1's engine. Vendored
  here as a frozen, unmodified snapshot -- exact upstream commit, clone date,
  and license verification recorded in PROVENANCE.md. Never edited; all door
  logic lives in our own files (hw_term.c + syncmoo1_*.c), which implement a
  new 1oom `hw` backend rather than patching the engine.

Master of Orion (the original game)
------------------------------------
- Master of Orion -- Simtex (developer) / MicroProse (publisher), 1993.
  All game design, artwork, text, music, and sound are their copyrighted
  work. syncmoo1 and the vendored 1oom engine do not include, distribute, or
  otherwise ship any of MoO1's original data files (the .LBX assets) -- the
  door requires a legally-owned copy of Master of Orion v1.3's data files to
  be supplied separately per install (see README.md). Sourcing that data is
  entirely the sysop's/player's responsibility, out of scope for this code.

syncmoo1's own code (this directory, outside 1oom/)
-----------------------------------------------------
- hw_term.c -- the 1oom `hw` backend: delegates 1oom's video/event/mouse/
  audio/timing hooks to the modules below instead of a native SDL/Allegro
  backend.
- syncmoo1_io.c/.h -- terminal present path (sixel encode via termgfx,
  de-dupe, DSR-ACK pacing), out-buffer, term enter/probe/leave.
- syncmoo1_input.c/.h -- socket read loop, ESC/CSI/APC state machine, key +
  mouse decode, capability-probe reply parsing.
- syncmoo1_door.c/.h -- DOOR32.SYS / -s<fd> dropfile, splash, argv sanitize,
  hangup.
- syncmoo1_config.c/.h -- per-user -home sandbox, shared MoO1 LBX data-path
  resolution.
- syncmoo1_map.c/.h -- pure keymap and mouse cell/pixel -> game-coordinate
  mapping functions (unit-tested in tests/).
- syncmoo1.h -- the single cross-module contract shared by all of the above.

Shared rendering/transport library (../termgfx)
-------------------------------------------------
syncmoo1 links the same `termgfx` library as ../syncdoom, ../syncduke, and
../syncconquer: sixel/JXL encoding, the SyncTERM APC image-cache + audio
transport, capability probing, DSR-ACK pacing, and `sbbs_node`. Its own
license/attribution lineage is documented in ../termgfx (no separate CREDITS
there); notably for the text render tier:
- doom-cli -- Nicholas Fraser (ludocode). (GPL-2.0)
  https://github.com/ludocode/doom-cli
  termgfx's text/block glyph render tiers (half/quadrant/sextant, color
  quantization and dithering) are lifted and adapted from doom-cli's
  doomgeneric_cli.c, per ../termgfx/text.c's own file-header attribution.
  syncmoo1's M1 milestone targets the sixel tier; this text-tier code ships
  in the shared library and is available to syncmoo1 for free, though it is
  not a tuned/verified M1 deliverable on its own (see README.md).

SyncTERM -- Stephen Hurd ("Deuce") and contributors -- implements the
APC image-cache + sixel + audio terminal graphics protocol syncmoo1 renders
to.
